com.crawljax.core.state
Class StateVertix

java.lang.Object
  com.crawljax.core.state.StateVertix
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class StateVertix
extends Object
implements Serializable

The state vertix class which represents a state in the browser. This class implements the Iterable interface because on a StateVertix it is possible to iterate over the possible CandidateElements found in this state. When iterating over the possible candidate elements every time a candidate is returned its removed from the list so it is a one time only access to the candidates.

pollCandidateCrawlAction

public CandidateCrawlAction pollCandidateCrawlAction(Crawler requestingCrawler,
                                                     CrawlQueueManager manager)
This is the main work divider function, calling this function will first look at the registeedCandidateActions to see if the current Crawler has already registered itself at one of the jobs. Second it tries to see if the current crawler is not already processing one of the actions and return that action and last it tries to find an unregistered candidate. If all else fails it tries to return a action that is registered by an other crawler and disables that crawler.

Parameters:
requestingCrawler - the Crawler placing the request for the Action
manager - the manager that can be used to remove a crawler from the queue.
Returns:
the action that needs to be performed by the Crawler.
